MODIFICATIONS:
- Applied fix from PR #21 (https://github.com/imbus/robotframework-debug/pull/21)
  * Fixed AttributeError in keywords command when KeywordDoc lacks shortdoc attribute
  * Modified debugcmd.py to check for shortdoc existence before accessing it
  * Added proper handling for keywords without documentation

REASON FOR VENDORING:
The upstream project is no longer actively maintained, and critical bug fixes
(such as PR #21) are not being merged. This vendored version ensures the
library remains functional for yarf's requirements.

The vendored code includes all modules from the RobotDebug package:
- cmdcompleter.py (command completion functionality)
- debugcmd.py (debug commands and REPL functionality)
- globals.py (global variables and state)
- history_app.py (command history management)
- lexer.py (syntax highlighting)
- prompttoolkitcmd.py (prompt toolkit integration)
- RobotDebug.py (main debug library interface)
- robotkeyword.py (Robot Framework keyword handling)
- robotlib.py (Robot Framework library utilities)
- shell.py (shell interface)
- sourcelines.py (source code display)
- styles.py (styling configuration)
- version.py (version information)

All original copyright notices and attribution are preserved.
